{"id":"eshbaal","term":"Eshbaal","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Man of Baal, the fourth son of king Saul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:33\">1 Chr. 8:33</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 9:39\">9:39</a>). He is also called Ish-bosheth (q.v.), <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Samuel 2:8\">2 Sam. 2:8</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 8:33","1 Chronicles 9:39","2 Samuel 2:8"]}